description: The Raptor, a steel inverted roller coaster with six inversions including a vertical loop, a zero-g roll, and an inline twist, was opened in 2002. It was manufactured by Bolliger & Mabillard and features a top speed of 57 miles per hour (92 km/h) and a 100-foot (30 m) drop.
label: INSERT INTO `Roller Coaster Information` (`Roller Coaster`, `Opened`, `Manufacturer`, `Description`) VALUES ('The Raptor', '2002', 'Bolliger & Mabillard', 'A steel inverted roller coaster. The Raptor has six inversions, including a vertical loop, a zero-g roll, and an inline twist. It also features a top speed of 57 miles per hour (92 km/h) and a 100-foot (30 m) drop.')

rows: A Boomerang Shuttle roller coaster . This ride is located on the edge of Fun Lake in the Darien Square section of the park . The coaster features a 120-foot ( 37 m ) tall backwards lift hill , a cobra roll and a loop . The train passes both forwards and backwards through both inversion elements

A steel kiddie roller coaster . Formerly called Ladybug and Nessie the Dreamy Dragon while it was part of Adventure Land for Kids . The ride was also part of the Tiny Trio and used to be called Brain Teaser . In 2012 , the train was remodeled to look like an owl and the ride was given the name Hoot N Holler so that it would fit in with the new Rowdy 's Ridge theme

A steel Suspended Looping Coaster , which is considered to be New York 's only Suspended Looping Coaster . This ride is approximately 120 feet ( 37 m ) with 5 inversions including a heart-loop ( half loop followed by twist followed by another half loop )

A Motorbike roller coaster which was the first of its kind in the United States . The Orange County Choppers branding was removed in 2010 . The coaster launches riders from 0 to 40 miles per hour ( 0 to 64 km/h ) in several seconds up to the top , followed by dips and turns on the way down before reaching the brakes
A wooden roller coaster . The Predator currently holds the title of New York 's largest wooden roller coaster . In 2010 , used trains from The Voyage were added to the ride

A steel Mega Coaster , formerly known as Superman - Ride of Steel . With a top height of 208 feet ( 63 m ) , and a maximum speed of 72 miles per hour ( 116 km/h ) , the ride is the tallest in New York State and one of Darien Lake 's largest attractions

A steel looping roller coaster . The Viper was the first coaster in the world with 5 inversions . Originally painted all black , the track was painted green when Six Flags took over and painted black in 2010

A Gerstlauer Euro-Fighter . Tantrum features a 98-foot vertical lift hill with a 97-degree drop , a pretzel inversion , a bunny hop , an Immelman turn and a tilted loop . It reaches a top speed of 52 miles per hour ( 84 km/h )
A steel looping roller coaster. Dragon Fire features a 90-foot vertical loop, a corkscrew and several camelbacks.
A wooden roller coaster. Wild Beast reaches a top speed of 60 miles per hour (97 km/h) and features several drops and turns throughout the ride.
A wooden roller coaster. Thunderbolt features a 70-foot (21 m) drop and reaches a top speed of 55 miles per hour (89 km/h).
A steel inverted roller coaster. Kong features a 124-foot (38 m) drop and reaches a top speed of 65 miles per hour (105 km/h). Riders experience several inversions throughout the ride.
A steel inverted roller coaster. Batman: The Ride features a 115-foot (35 m) tall vertical loop, a zero-g roll, and several corkscrews. Riders experience several inversions throughout the ride.
A steel hyper coaster. Steel Force features a 205-foot (62 m) drop and reaches a top speed of 75 miles per hour (121 km/h). The ride lasts over 3 minutes and includes several airtime hills.
A steel inverted roller coaster. Raptor features a 137-foot (42 m) drop and reaches a top speed of 57 miles per hour (92 km/h). The ride includes several inversions and tight turns.

A steel flying roller coaster. Superman: Ultimate Flight features a 100-foot (30 m) tall pretzel loop and reaches a top speed of 60 miles per hour (97 km/h). Riders experience several inversions while flying through the ride.
A wooden hybrid coaster. Goliath features a 180-foot (55 m) drop and reaches a top speed of 72 miles per hour (116 km/h). The ride includes several inversions and is known for its smooth track.

A steel accelerator coaster. Top Thrill Dragster reaches a top speed of 120 miles per hour (190 km/h) in just 3.8 seconds and includes a 420-foot (130 m) tall top hat element. Riders experience intense positive G-forces during the ride.
